COVID-19 infections are increasing rapidly in Gauteng. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - COVID-19 infections are increasing rapidly in Gauteng. The total number of confirmed coronavirus cases in the province sits at 45,944, with 10,534 recoveries and 244 deaths. READ: A third of COVID-19 patients have at least one comorbidity The total number of infections in South Africa is at 159,333. WATCH: Ramaphosa interacts with communities on COVID-19 More than 76,000 people have recovered from the virus. The Health Department reported 92 new COVID-19 related deaths, bringing the death toll to 2749. Some experts say Gauteng almost at its COVID-19 peak. The province is battling chilly winter temperatures. #eNCA reporter, Nqobile Madlala is checking out quarantine sites. #Courtesy #DStv403 Health Media Release 1 July 2020 v1 (1) by eNCA.com on Scribd 